                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/8666757/karthik-v",
                "reputation": 51,
                "display_name": "Karthik V"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1506292384,
            "creation_date": 1506292384,
            "body": "<p>For the java.awt, I found this android port - <a href=\"https://bitbucket.org/mkmatlock/android-pdfbox/downloads/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://bitbucket.org/mkmatlock/android-pdfbox/downloads/<\/a> (look for the android-awt-*.jar and throw it into your project as a library dependency). I was looking for a pdfbox port (which uses awt internally) when I found that. I haven't tested it thoroughly but it seems to suppress my compile errors.<\/p>\n\n<p>I'm still looking for the javax.imageio port, will update when I find one.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 46395498,
            "question_id": 13709030
        }
